title: Issue with building pytorch from source
body_html:
Issue description

While compiling pytorch tag version v0.4.1 from source with I am getting following error

error: no matching function for call to
'onnxifi_load'
onnxifi_load(ONNXIFI_LOADER_FLAG_VERSION_1_0, nullptr, nullptr, &core);

Provide a short description.

Code example

On executing the following command after installing all dependencies for pytorch
MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=10.12 CC=clang CXX=clang++ python setup.py install
I am getting following error for building
pytorch/caffe2/onnx/onnxifi_init.cc:14:9: error: no matching function for call to
'onnxifi_load'
onnxifi_load(ONNXIFI_LOADER_FLAG_VERSION_1_0, nullptr, nullptr, &core);

System Info

OS: Mac OSX 10.12.6
GCC version: Could not collect
CMake version: version 3.12.0

  • PyTorch or Caffe2: PyTorch
  • How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): Source
    Python version: 3.6
    CUDA runtime version: 9.2.64
    GPU models and configuration: Could not collect
    Nvidia driver version: Could not collect
    cuDNN version: Probably one of the following:
    /usr/local/cuda/lib/libcudnn.5.dylib
    /usr/local/cuda/lib/libcudnn.dylib
    /usr/local/cuda/lib/libcudnn_static.a
    /usr/local/cuda/lib64/libcudnn.5.dylib
    /usr/local/cuda/lib64/libcudnn.dylib
    /usr/local/cuda/lib64/libcudnn_static.a

Versions of relevant libraries:
[pip3] numpy (1.15.0)
[conda] # packages in environment at
